Ad Text:
Power BI Consultant – Power Apps & Automation Focus

We are seeking a motivated and highly skilled Power BI Consultant for an immediate-start 3-month contract engagement. The ideal candidate will bring deep experience in building impactful business intelligence solutions, with advanced capabilities in Data Modelling, Visualisation & Dashboards.

This role is particularly suited to candidates who excel at bridging technical development with business needs, and who can deliver end-to-end analytics and low-code solutions with minimal supervision in fast-paced, project-driven environments.

Key Responsibilities:

Dashboard Design & Development: Build, enhance, and maintain enterprise-grade Power BI dashboards and reports, applying UX best practices and data visualisation principles.

Design, develop, and maintain Power BI dashboards and reports that deliver clear and actionable insights.

Build and optimise data models (DAX, Power Query, M language) to support enterprise-level reporting.

Experience with Fabric & SAP data highly valued.

Partner with stakeholders to gather requirements, translate them into technical specifications, and deliver solutions that meet business needs.

Implement best practices for Power BI governance, including dataset certification, row-level security, and workspace management.

Integration & Sourcing: Connect Power BI reports to a variety of data sources including SQL Server, SharePoint, Excel, and APIs.

Collaboration & Delivery: Engage with stakeholders to gather requirements, prototype solutions, and support user testing and deployment.

Documentation & Support: Develop high-quality documentation for solutions, processes, and user guides, enabling sustainable handover and knowledge sharing.

Governance & Best Practice: Apply governance frameworks, naming conventions, and security best practices across Power Platform solutions.

Requirements:

Must have Australian working rights.

Min Experience: 5–years plus in analytics, reporting, or business intelligence roles.

Proven experience delivering Power BI solutions in an enterprise setting.

Technical Skills:

Advanced proficiency in DAX, Fabric, SAP, Power Query (M), and Data Modelling.

Implement best practices for Power BI governance, including dataset certification, row-level security, and workspace management.

Drive automation and efficiency by integrating data from multiple sources (SQL, Azure, Databricks, Snowflake cloud-based warehouses).

Comfortable working with REST APIs and integrating various data services.

Experience with PBI training desirable.

Stakeholder Engagement: Confident communicator with the ability to understand business problems and translate them into technical solutions.

Availability: Must be available for immediate start on a full-time 3-month contract.

Delivery Experience: Prior experience in agile or hybrid delivery models, ideally with project exposure in finance, operations, or HR domains.

Preferred Qualifications:

Exposure to Power BI Service administration and workspace management.

Experience of having worked with Fabric & SAP is a bonus.

Why Join Us?

Impactful Projects: Work on high-visibility business intelligence solutions that empower enterprise decision-making.

Modern Tooling: Leverage the latest in Power Platform technologies in a supportive environment.

Agile, Fast-Moving Culture: Join a team that delivers meaningful outcomes quickly, with direct stakeholder engagement.

Flexible Work Environment: Hybrid contract with a pragmatic and delivery-first approach.

This ASX listed SaaS business is currently in an exciting phase of growth and looking for a versatile Business Analyst who thrives at the intersection of finance, product, and operations.

This is an exceptional opportunity to work across disciplines supporting product development, financial modelling, process improvement, and executive-level reporting, while contributing to a 0→1 product and partnership build.

What You’ll Do
Structured Analysis & Requirements: Lead discovery with stakeholders, break down complex problems into actionable requirements, user stories, and acceptance criteria.
Financial & Commercial Analysis: Support pricing, costing, forecasting, and scenario modelling to inform commercial decisions.
Process & Compliance Support: Map As-Is and To-Be processes, contribute to operational controls, and support compliance-aligned workflows.
Product & Technical Collaboration: Work with Product, UX, and Engineering teams to shape early designs, user journeys, and integration assumptions.
Program Delivery Support: Maintain program artefacts, contribute to backlog prioritisation, support UAT, and prepare executive summaries.
What We’re Looking For
4–7+ years in Business Analysis, Product Analysis, Operations, Consulting, or related roles.
Strong analytical and quantitative skills (Excel advanced; Power BI; SQL a plus).
Experience with process mapping tools and methodologies (BPMN/UML).
Comfortable collaborating across finance, product, engineering, and senior leadership.
Curious, adaptable, and ready to take on varied responsibilities.
Experience in payments, banking, fintech, or SaaS would be a bonus
What Success Looks Like
Clear, actionable documentation accelerating product and process decisions.
High-quality financial and commercial analyses supporting strategic outcomes.
Smooth program delivery and positive stakeholder engagement.
Why join

Initial 12 month fixed term contact (annual leave and other benefits included) paying $150K - $170K + Super
Be part of a collaborative, pragmatic, and outcome-driven team.
Work on meaningful, high-impact projects with exposure to senior stakeholders.
Competitive salary package and the chance to influence a critical strategic partnership.
If you’re ready to thrive in a dynamic, growth-focused business and make a real impact, apply now with your CV.

Job Title: Senior Lecturer in Business Information Systems
Ad Text:
Classification: Academic Level C
Salary package: $146,007 - $162,281 per annum plus 17% superannuation 

Terms: Full time, Continuing

Position Description and Selection Criteria: PD & PEWER Level C Senior Lecturer in Business Information Systems.pdf



Position overview 

The Research School of Management in the ANU College of Business and Economics aims to create and share management knowledge that makes a difference to organisations and society. Nine academics with affiliations to our School are listed among the 2025 Stanford/Elsevier Top 2% Scientists.

To continue the current growth trajectory, we are seeking to recruit a Senior Lecturer (Level C) in the field of Business Information Systems. The successful applicant will conduct research of international standing and actively contribute to undergraduate and postgraduate teaching in the School. They will have a strong work ethic, a practical approach, and be passionate about the quality of their work. The successful applicant will join a strong team of academics who publish in top international journals and hold external competitive grants. The School and College provide an excellent research environment, including favourable teaching load and internal research support. 

The position is open to international applicants. The successful applicant must be available to commence work in Canberra, Australia by mid-2026. The successful applicant will be offered relocation assistance as per ANU Policy.

We have a strong equal opportunity culture. We encourage all applicants particularly, female, Aboriginal or Torres Strait Islander applicants. 

For further information, please contact Associate Professor Ashkan Zarghami, E: ashkan.zarghami@anu.edu.au

College overview 

The Australian National University (ANU) is one of the world’s great universities, ranking 32nd in the 2026 QS World University Rankings. The Research School of Management sits within the ANU College of Business and Economics. The College educates the next generation of business leaders, professional economists and academics. Our graduates have the knowledge and skills to lead organisations, design public policy, and research the big issues of business and economy.

Located in the national capital, we engage deeply with the business and policy communities. Our academics lead public debate on the critical issues of our time through their research, which is both long term and strategic in focus. Our internationally diverse student body is evenly divided between undergraduate and postgraduate study, and we have a large doctoral program. Our alumni are found in the world's leading companies, policy agencies and universities. 

We strongly believe that the way in which we operate is defined by our Values and Behaviours and encourage you to apply if you are looking for a workplace that encourages respect, collegiality and excellence. 

The University actively encourages applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people. For more information on employment opportunities, contact our Indigenous Employment Consultant on indigenous.employment@anu.edu.au.

ANU values diversity and inclusion and believes employment opportunities must not be limited by socio-economic background, race, religion or gender. For more information about staff equity at ANU, visit https://services.anu.edu.au/business-units/human-resources-division/equity-and-diversity 

Application information

In order to apply for this role please make sure that you upload the following documents:

A statement (3 pages max) addressing the selection criteria.
A current curriculum vitae (CV) which includes the names and contact details of at least three referees (preferably including a current or previous supervisor). If your CV does not include referees you can complete these online when prompted in the application form.
Other documents, if required.

Applications which do not address the selection criteria may not be considered for the position.

Please note: The successful candidate will be required to undergo a background check during the recruitment process.  An offer of employment is conditional on satisfactory results.

 Closing date: Thursday, 15 January 2026, 11.55 (Canberra Time)
